name: UMass Fine Arts Center
directions:
There are a couple ways to get to this single stall, lockable, gender neutral bathroom. 

If you are unfamiliar with the Fine Arts Center, the easiest way to get there is to go into the main entrance to the concert hall, and go down the right isle passing the ticket booth. You will see a men's restroom on your left. Keep going until you see a door on your right with a wheelchair ramp. Enter the doors. Inside you will find an elevator straight ahead, and a drinking fountain to the left. Just past the drinking fountain is the bathroom.

You can also get to the bathroom by going through the FAC by rooms 44 and 36, but I do not recommend that unless you know your way around. (The FAC is a maze).
comment: If you choose to use the restroom during a production/play/concert, there will be EMTs sitting in the room next to the elevator. They won't bother you, but I am putting that in so it doesn't catch you off-guard.
